 stop the incident from spreading further and limit damage.", DifficultyLevel.BEGINNER),
                QuizQuestion("irq4", "Which document establishes the formal process for handling security incidents?",
                    ["Business continuity plan", "Incident Response Plan", "Disaster recovery plan", "Network diagram"], 1,
                    "The Incident Response Plan defines roles, procedures, and workflows for handling incidents.", DifficultyLevel.BEGINNER),
                QuizQuestion("irq5", "What is the purpose of a honeypot?",
                    ["Store sensitive data securely", "Detect and divert attackers from real systems", "Encrypt network traffic", "Speed up network performance"], 1,
                    "Honeypots attract attackers to decoy systems, providing early warning and intelligence.", DifficultyLevel.INTERMEDIATE),
                QuizQuestion("irq6", "What is SOAR?",
                    ["Security Operations and Response", "Security Orchestration, Automation and Response", "System Operations and Recovery", "Security Operations Analysis Report"], 1,
                    "SOAR platforms automate incident response workflows, case management, and threat intel.", DifficultyLevel.INTERMEDIATE),
                QuizQuestion("irq7", "During evidence collection, what is the chain of custody?",
                    ["A physical chain", "Documentation tracking evidence handling from collection to presentation", "Network topology map", "Encryption key"], 1,
                    "Chain of custody documents who handled evidence, when, and why to ensure admissibility.", DifficultyLevel.INTERMEDIATE),
                QuizQuestion("irq8", "What is the difference between eradication and containment?",
                    ["They are the same", "Containment stops spread; eradication removes the threat completely", "Eradication happens first", "Containment removes the threat"], 1,
                    "Containment is temporary; eradication completely removes the threat from the environment.", DifficultyLevel.INTERMEDIATE),
                QuizQuestion("irq9", "Which technique is used for root cause analysis?",
                    ["Brute force", "5 Whys", "Social engineering", "Port scanning"], 1,
                    "5 Whys is a root cause analysis technique asking 'why' repeatedly to identify root causes.", DifficultyLevel.INTERMEDIATE),
                QuizQuestion("irq10", "What is the primary purpose of post-incident activity?",
                    ["Blame individuals", "Learn from the incident and improve defenses", "Ignore the incident", "Delete all evidence"], 1,
                    "Post-incident activity focuses on lessons learned and continuous improvement.", DifficultyLevel.BEGINNER),
                QuizQuestion("irq11", "What should be done first when ransomware is detected?",
                    ["Pay the ransom immediately", "Isolate affected systems to prevent spread", "Delete all files", "Notify the media"], 1,
                    "Immediate isolation prevents the ransomware from spreading to other systems.", DifficultyLevel.BEGINNER),
                QuizQuestion("irq12", "What does EDR stand for?",
                    ["Electronic Data Recovery", "Endpoint Detection and Response", "Encrypted Data Repository", "Enterprise Disaster Recovery"], 1,
                    "EDR (Endpoint Detection and Response) monitors endpoints for threats and enables response.", DifficultyLevel.BEGINNER),
                QuizQuestion("irq13", "What is the recommended approach for evidence preservation?",
                    ["Modify files to understand the attack", "Create forensic images and maintain chain of custody", "Delete suspicious files", "Restart the system immediately"], 1,
                    "Forensic images preserve original evidence integrity; chain of custody ensures admissibility.", DifficultyLevel.INTERMEDIATE),
            ],
        ),
    )

